    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and slice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>kidney beans</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lamb-and-bean-biryani-with-mint-dressing/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a pot (with a matching lid) over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>mince </strong>and <strong>half </strong>the <strong>sliced onion </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)<strong> </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>Tip: Drain any excess oil from the pan and discard!</p><p>Peel and finely chop your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lamb-and-bean-biryani-with-mint-dressing/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once browned, add your <strong>curry powder</strong>, <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and <strong>tomato paste </strong>and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lamb-and-bean-biryani-with-mint-dressing/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>brown rice </strong>to the pan and stir to coat the grains in the spice and oil</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lamb-and-bean-biryani-with-mint-dressing/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once coated, add the <strong>drained kidney beans </strong>and your <strong>beef stock mix </strong>with 350ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[525ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lamb-and-bean-biryani-with-mint-dressing/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook, covered, for 35-38 min or until the water has absorbed and the mince is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>biryani</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of water if the rice is not cooked or the mixture is a little dry</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lamb-and-bean-biryani-with-mint-dressing/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the rice cooks, combine your <strong>red wine vinegar </strong>with a 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong> in a small bowl</p><p>Add the <strong>reserved sliced onion </strong>to the bowl and set aside to pickle \u2013 this is your <strong>quick-pickled onion</strong></p><p>Once the rice is tender, remove the pot from the heat and keep covered for a further 5 min before serving</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lamb-and-bean-biryani-with-mint-dressing/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Season the <strong>biryani </strong>with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and fluff the with a fork</p><p>Serve the <strong>biriyani </strong>and drizzle with your <strong>natural yoghurt</strong></p><p>Top with the <strong>quick-pickled onion </strong>and finish with a grind of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
